<br>
I suppose if you don't value time, friends, family, your job than yes, you could be addicted to EQ.  But if you don't value those things, you could be addicted to anything that convinces you it is better than facing real life. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.cogeco.ca/~lady_shagswell/foxsig6.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
